# Bench profile: SELEC MFM384 — poll V1N phase voltage (FC04 reg 0, float32) at 1 Hz.
# Usage:
#   idf.py -DSDKCONFIG_DEFAULTS="sdkconfig.defaults;sdkconfig.defaults.mfm384-volt" build flash monitor
# Rationale (cross-checked vs southern-rnd/ETS-LORA-Test, same RAK3112+MFM384, tested working):
# that build reads the MFM384 entirely over FC04 INPUT registers, voltage-first map (V1N @ reg 0).
# FC04 reg 0 is the best linkcheck: present + non-zero whenever the meter is powered. The raw hex
# words are logged, so word order is readable by eye (ABCD vs CDAB) — the two reference repos
# disagree (RAK3312=ABCD, ETS=CDAB); flip CONFIG_APP_MODBUS_POLL_FLOAT_CDAB=y if the value is wrong.
CONFIG_APP_MODBUS_POLL_ON_BOOT=y
CONFIG_APP_MODBUS_POLL_UNIT=1
CONFIG_APP_MODBUS_POLL_BAUD=9600
CONFIG_APP_MODBUS_POLL_FC=4
CONFIG_APP_MODBUS_POLL_REG=0
CONFIG_APP_MODBUS_POLL_FLOAT=y
CONFIG_APP_MODBUS_POLL_FLOAT_CDAB=n
